      "body": "JSON-RPC 1.0 was bidirectional, so would have fit well. Unfortunately, that functionality was removed in 2.0. I have a pullrequest for GBT longpolling open, but I don't know how well it would work for events in general (seems too easy to miss an event). Chunked encoding could be used to simply stream data, but I think most clients won't give you anything until it's all received. Not sure how complex websockets are...\n",
